# Qube — Cursor project index

**Canonical rules and long-form directives:** `.clinerules` (source of truth).

**Domain rules (Cursor `.mdc`):** `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` — `native_engine.mdc` (dual-engine inference, execution policy, prompt template router, template_override + model_override_store self-heal, reasoning detection, debug stack, NVIDIA/Nemotron auto ChatML preference in Auto mode, and NVIDIA-specific internal prompt policy), `tools-diagnostics.mdc` (CLI: `run_ablation`, `view_llm_logs`, `llm_prompt_diff`; ablation may persist `~/.qube/model_overrides.json`), `ui-rules.mdc` (Think toggle / telemetry polling + service-backed Model Manager capability chips + tooltip reliability contract), `audio-workers.mdc` (routing, prompting, TTS/interrupt safety), `model_manager.mdc` (Hub browsing/download flow + worker/thread rules + isolated capability detection/cache pipeline + official publisher branding), `rag-engine.mdc` (RAG + memory + router constraints).

**Model Manager styling note (critical):** For right-panel card background parity (metadata/download/README) use objectName-scoped styles in `ModelManagerView._apply_hub_list_surface(...)` and set `QTextBrowser` + viewport palette together; generic class/global QSS may override expected surfaces.

**Tooltip reliability note (critical):** On Linux frameless/translucent shells, native `QToolTip` can render inconsistently across widgets/themes. Use `core/qube_tooltip.py` (`QubeApplication` + `QubeToolTipController`) as the single tooltip rendering path; keep tooltip text plain in views and sync theme via `qube_tooltip_set_theme(...)` at startup and in `MainWindow._toggle_theme`.

**Primary / Brand action button note (critical):** Reusable primary / brand action buttons (Wakeword Test Lab, Use Selected, Delete, Retest, primary_btn in the testbed, Model Manager Download / Load More, etc.) are styled by the single helper **`ui/components/brand_buttons.py`** → `apply_brand_primary(btn, icon_name=None)` / `apply_brand_success(btn, icon_name=None)` / `apply_brand_danger(btn, icon_name=None)`. The helper installs a widget-level QSS on the button (which has the highest specificity of any QSS source in Qt and cannot be overridden by app-level rules or the widget palette), re-sets the legacy `class` dynamic property for backward-compat, optionally renders a qtawesome icon tinted to `BRAND_FG_COLOR[variant]` (+ `BRAND_DISABLED_FG_COLOR` for the disabled state) so the icon always matches the text color, and runs `unpolish` + `polish` + `update`. **Do not style these buttons with `setProperty("class", "PrimaryActionButton Brand...Button")` alone** — on some Qt builds / platform styles the app-level `QPushButton[class~="..."]` rules, even with `!important`, silently lose the `background-color` race against the generic `QPushButton { background-color: #ffffff; color: #1e293b; }` rule in light theme and render the button as white-on-off-white. **Do not set a brand button icon with a hard-coded hex color** (e.g. `btn.setIcon(qta.icon("fa5s.download", color="#8b5cf6"))` on a brand-purple button renders the icon invisibly in the bg color); pass `icon_name="fa5s.download"` to `apply_brand_*` instead, or read `brand_fg_color(variant)` for call sites that need custom qtawesome options. For mode-switching buttons (Model Manager Download `download` / `play` / `times`), route both variant AND icon through a single mode helper like `_apply_download_action_button_style` so they stay in lockstep; `refresh_button_themes` then only needs to re-invoke that helper for the current mode (no manual `setIcon` on theme toggle). `ui/components/brand_buttons.py` exists specifically to make both the white-on-off-white bg bug AND the icon-blends-into-bg bug unreachable. **Every new primary / success / danger filled button must go through that helper.** The one intentional exception is `WakewordTestbedDialog.apply_btn`, which is styled by container-level QSS driven by its `result_tone` dynamic property (`#WakewordApplyButton[result_tone="success|caution|failure"]`); do not route it through the helper because widget-level QSS would defeat the container's tone variants. The old `QPushButton[class~="PrimaryActionButton|BrandXxxButton"]` rules in `assets/styles/base.qss` + `light.qss` are kept as a fallback for any code path that still uses `setProperty("class", ...)` directly, but they are NOT the primary rendering path anymore. See `.cursor/rules/ui-rules.mdc` → "Primary / Brand action buttons (critical)".

**Dropdown selector button note (critical):** Qt's `QPushButton` silently drops QSS `padding` / `text-align` for the **label** when an icon is attached with `setLayoutDirection(RightToLeft)` (common in the legacy `SettingsMenuButton + setIcon(fa chevron)` pattern used for Prestige dropdowns). It still honors `padding` for `sizeHint()` (so button height is correct), but the text hugs the left inner edge and the chevron hugs the right inner edge. The **same widget configuration also makes the button's surface render from the QWidget palette instead of the QSS `background-color`** on Linux / `QStyleSheetStyle` — so in light theme a Settings dropdown can appear as the same color as `#SettingsScrollArea` (the page background) even with `background-color: #ffffff !important;` on `#SettingsMenuButton`. The quirk is usually invisible on narrow buttons (≤~180 px) and suddenly obvious on wide ones (Settings → Wakeword / Audio Input / Audio Output / AI Engine / External Provider / Chat template). **Use `ui/components/selector_button.py` (`SelectorButton`, `objectName="QubeSelectorButton"`) for every wide dropdown-style button** — in Settings, Wakeword Test Lab, and any new page. It takes over text + chevron drawing via `paintEvent` and paints its own bezel via `style().drawControl(CE_PushButton, ...)`, so both the padding-ignored and palette-over-QSS bugs are bypassed by construction. Keep QSS `padding: 8px 15px;` and `PADDING_LEFT=15` aligned with the global `#SettingsMenuButton` rule; the custom paint uses `self.font()` so the global Inter/400 rule is inherited (do NOT manually resize the font). Because `SettingsView` is constructed before it is parented to `MainWindow`, `SelectorButton.showEvent` re-checks `self.window()._is_dark_theme` and re-applies the theme; theme toggles must call `SelectorButton.apply_theme(is_dark)` from `refresh_menu_themes(...)`. **Never** add a global `#SettingsMenuButton::menu-indicator { image: none; }` to `assets/styles/*.qss` — it cascades to every Prestige dropdown in the app; the selector suppresses its own menu-indicator locally via `#QubeSelectorButton::menu-indicator`. When adding a new dropdown to any view, go to `SelectorButton` directly — do NOT reintroduce the `QPushButton + setObjectName("SettingsMenuButton") + setLayoutDirection(RightToLeft) + setIcon(fa chevron)` pattern; that pattern is preserved in `MainWindow` toolbar for now only for historical stability and is on a quiet migration path.

**Native LLM inference debug (internal engine only, observer-only):** All optional; no prompt/sampling/stream changes. Logger: **`Qube.NativeLLM.Debug`**. Typical order after each completion: (1) **`QUBE_LLM_TOKEN_TRACE`** — live vs post-hoc vs sampler GT (`native_token_trace`, `native_sampler_gt`); (2) **`QUBE_LLM_CAUSALITY`** — `llm_execution_causality_report` (`llm_execution_causality`); (3) **`QUBE_LLM_COUNTERFACTUAL`** — analytical `llm_counterfactual_simulation` (`llm_counterfactual`). Baseline / parity: **`QUBE_LLM_DEBUG`** / **`QUBE_LLM_PROMPT_VALIDATE`** + **`QUBE_LLM_REFERENCE_JSON`** (optional `first_sampler_token_ids` for first-token diff). **Model reasoning profile (metadata only):** `core/model_reasoning_profile.py` classifies thinking-token support (**`detect_model_reasoning_profile`**: tokenizer scan with first-hit exit, GGUF **`tokenizer.chat_template`**, weak **`metadata_template`** hints, name/path heuristics; **`_llama_cpp_model`** = **`_model`** or **`model`**) + profile **`ExecutionMode`** (`direct` / `thinking` / `hybrid` / `unknown`); **`NativeLlamaEngine`** stores **`_execution_mode`** after load. **Think toggle sync:** **`main.py`** connects `native_llama_engine.load_finished` to `_on_native_model_load_finished`, which re-syncs `ConversationsView.refresh_think_toggle`; **`ConversationsView.showEvent`** re-syncs when returning to the screen. **Central execution policy:** `core/execution_policy.py` defines **`ExecutionPolicy`** via **`resolve_execution_policy(...)`** — profile + QSettings Think + **`engine_mode`**; telemetry **`ui_display_thinking`**; **`LLMWorker`** stream filters follow **`strip_thinking_output`**. **Prompt construction (observability bundle):** `core/prompt_template_router.py` — **`infer_template_type`** (chatml / llama3 / phi / mistral / jinja / fallback from **`tokenizer.chat_template`** + **`chat_format`**); **`apply_reasoning_injection`** (model-aware **`reasoning_mode`** text — no generic overlay); **`build_prompt_bundle`** = **`reconstruct_formatted_prompt`** + injection + merged stops, then **Phase 4** **`core/template_override.py`** (**`detect_template_override`**: model-name stops + assistant anchor; **`[LLM-TEMPLATE-OVERRIDE]`**), then **Phase 5** **`core/model_override_store.py`** (**`get_override`**: persisted **`LearnedOverride`** from ablation self-heal — merge **`extra_stop_tokens`** + anchor; **`[LLM-SELF-HEAL-APPLY]`**; policy fields in JSON are not applied in the router); logs **`[LLM-TEMPLATE]`** + **`[LLM-PROMPT-ROUTER]`** on **`Qube.PromptTemplateRouter`**; **`NativeLlamaEngine._prepare_validation_and_logs`** uses the bundle for validation / logs (**`create_chat_completion(messages=...)`** unchanged). **Load-time behavior profiling (internal):** `core/model_behavior.py` — ablation on model load (skipped when **`get_override(model_name)`** already has a persisted self-heal entry — **`[LLM-SELF-HEAL] skip ablation`**) → **`classify_model_behavior`** / **`resolve_behavior_override`** → **`get_execution_policy()`** may adjust execution fields; JSON **`llm_model_behavior_profile`** on **`Qube.NativeLLM.Debug`**. **Self-heal learning:** `core/prompt_ablation_harness.py` **`infer_override_from_ablation`** + **`store_override`** → **`~/.qube/model_overrides.json`**; **`[LLM-SELF-HEAL]`** when a new override is written. **Diagnostic-only:** `core/prompt_ablation_harness.py` + **`python -m tools.run_ablation`** — **`AblationReport`** (not per-request). Logs **`[LLM-DEBUG] execution_policy=...`**, **`[LLM-ABLATION] ...`**. See `.cursor/rules/native_engine.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/tools-diagnostics.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/ui-rules.mdc`.

Below is the **Section 3 directory treemap** (keep in sync with `.clinerules` Section 3 when you add files).

```text
Qube/
├── main.py                 # Entry point: NativeLlamaEngine, LLMWorker, MainWindow; load_finished → _on_native_model_load_finished → conversations Think refresh (refresh_think_toggle). Owns EnrichmentWorker + MemoryReflectionWorker lifecycle (start on boot, shutdown+wait on exit). _on_enrichment_context_ready caches per-turn provenance payload (session_id / last_user_msg_id / last_assistant_msg_id / rag_chunk_ids) and forwards it to enrichment_worker.enqueue at response_finished.
├── assets/                 # Static UI and Brand Assets (Immutable)
│   ├── fonts /             # Custom Inter font families.
│   ├── icons/              # App UI icons (chevrons/layout controls; keep backward-compat fallbacks where used).
│   ├── logos/              # Brand/publisher logos and app logo assets used by window/top bar + Model Manager branding.
│   ├── sounds/             # (Planned / not yet created) Notification chimes or UI sound effects.
│   ├── styles/             # base.qss (dark), light.qss — includes #SettingsMenuButton and :disabled states for locked Prestige dropdowns.
│   └── screenshots/        # Screenshots of the app for Github
├── ui/                     # Presentation Layer (Dumb Components)
│   ├── main_window.py      # Frameless shell, nav, global toolbar (incl. LOCAL LLM SettingsMenuButton + Prestige menus), optimistic LOCAL LLM picker label + zero-shift 4px load progress bar + stale load-finish guard, top bar, theme toggle; passes native_engine into TelemetryView for read-only capability telemetry. Nav order: Chat (0) / Library (1) / Memories (2, fa5s.brain — MemoryManagerView) / Telemetry (3) / Models (4) / Settings (5); _route_view + _toggle_theme call memory_manager_view.refresh_theme on theme change.
│   ├── router_dashboard.py # Visualizations go into the Telemetry screen
│   ├── components/         # Reusable custom UI components.
│   │   ├── memory_debug_panel.py # Live UI debug panel exposing internal ranking math (semantic distance, confidence, strength, and final score) of the memory retrieval pipeline
│   │   ├── source_viewer.py # UI dialog component for displaying the raw text of cited RAG documents and web sources
│   │   ├── toggle.py       # Toggle (custom design) we use in the UI
│   │   ├── prestige_dialog.py # Frameless dark/light confirmation & input dialog (replaces QMessageBox/QInputDialog everywhere)
│   │   ├── readability_toolbar_styles.py # Shared QSS for A−/A+ font controls (Conversations + Library preview toolbars).
│   │   ├── sidebar_list_qss.py # apply_sidebar_row_title_colors: row QLabel colors for History/Library setItemWidget lists (QSS ::item selectors are unreliable).
│   │   ├── selector_button.py # SelectorButton (#QubeSelectorButton): dropdown-style QPushButton with custom-painted text + chevron; bypasses Qt’s QSS-padding-ignored quirk on icon buttons with RightToLeft layout; showEvent re-syncs theme against window()._is_dark_theme; QSS `padding: 8px 15px;` drives sizeHint parity with #SettingsMenuButton.
│   │   ├── brand_buttons.py # apply_brand_primary / apply_brand_success / apply_brand_danger (+ optional icon_name auto-tinted to BRAND_FG_COLOR[variant] so filled brand icons stay legible): widget-level QSS helper for the Prestige primary / success / danger filled action buttons (Wakeword Test Lab, Use Selected, Delete, primary_btn, Model Manager Download / Load Model / Cancel, etc.); widget-level QSS beats app-level `[class~="..."]` + `!important` which silently lost the bg race in light theme on some platform styles.
│   │   └── llm_debug_log_panel.py # Optional live llm_debug.log panel for Telemetry view (QUBE_LLM_LOG_UI=1)
│   └── views/              # isolated widget files for each major screen
│       ├── conversations_view.py # PrestigeDialog, chat stages, Think toggle (telemetry ui_display_thinking; refresh_think_toggle on load_finished via main + showEvent).
│       ├── library_view.py # Knowledge base screen
│       ├── memory_manager_view.py # Memory v6 Phase C — user-facing inspector + editor for the LanceDB memory store. Filters: T3.4 two-level SelectorButton filter — tier dropdown (All / Preferences / Knowledge / Episodes / Context, derived from the LanceDB source string via _tier_from_source) paired with the existing category dropdown (T3.2 adds "episode" alongside preference/identity/project/knowledge/context) / Flagged-only toggle / text search. Top "Flagged for review" pseudo-section followed by category-grouped sections; per-row Edit (PrestigeDialog input) / Flag-Unflag / Delete (PrestigeDialog confirm + apply_brand_danger). Each row card renders a MemoryRowTierBadge (PREF green / KNOW purple / EP blue / CTX slate) styled widget-level (brand-button rule) alongside the existing MemoryRowCategoryBadge; episode rows render a MemoryRowTopics line ("topics: a · b · c") under the provenance slot so session summaries are visually distinct from atomic facts. Bulk "Delete all visible" (apply_brand_danger). Off-thread MemoryManagerWorker (QThread + Queue) handles every store.table read / delete / re-add. Every delete also writes the row content+vector into core/memory_negative_list so the same memory cannot be recreated by the next extraction pass. refresh_theme(is_dark) re-applies row + section + control palette (including the tier selector) on theme toggle.
│       ├── settings_view.py # Settings: dual-engine (engine vs external provider), GPU offload + CPU thread pool QSliders (caps from gpu_layers_cap / cpu_threads), ~75% hardware defaults on first run (missing QSettings keys), local GGUF list + Use/Delete, PrestigeDialog only (no QMessageBox).
│       ├── telemetry_view.py # Telemetry screen (hardware graphs, router metrics, optional LLM debug panel); “Native LLM — Model capability” card polls NativeLlamaEngine.get_model_reasoning_telemetry() when internal engine is wired.
│       └── model_manager_view.py # App Store-style Hub browser (search, README, quant dropdown), local GGUF library, download/cancel flow, and capability chips sourced from ModelCapabilityService for sidebar + mainstage with progressive post-README enrichment.
├── core/                   # System, Hardware, Preferences, Network, and Native LLM helpers (31 files; alphabetical)
│   ├── app_settings.py     # QSettings: engine mode, internal GGUF path, internal_n_gpu_layers (VRAM cap + optional 75% default), internal_n_threads (logical CPU cap + optional 75% default), llm_models_dir, chat format token, etc.
│   ├── audio_utils.py      # PyAudio device discovery and index mapping.
│   ├── cpu_threads.py      # Logical CPU count (psutil/os), max_cpu_threads_for_ui, default_internal_n_threads (~75% of cores) for native llama.cpp n_threads.
│   ├── database.py         # SQLite session/document API for the UI.
│   ├── execution_policy.py # Central ExecutionPolicy + resolve_execution_policy (model profile + user Think override + engine_mode); reasoning allowance, UI/TTS strip flags, enforcement soft/hard (no prompt/sampling changes).
│   ├── gpu_layers_cap.py   # VRAM detection + max_safe_n_gpu_layers + default_internal_n_gpu_layers_suggested (~75% of cap) for first-run GPU slider default.
│   ├── gpu_monitor.py      # GPUMonitor: NVIDIA (pynvml) / Linux sysfs / Windows perf for load % telemetry (not VRAM caps).
│   ├── llm_counterfactual.py # QUBE_LLM_COUNTERFACTUAL: analytical what-if scenarios (no inference) — one intervention at a time; emits llm_counterfactual_simulation.
│   ├── llm_debug_sink.py   # Rotating file handler for Qube.NativeLLM.Debug -> logs/llm_debug.log (terminal quiet via logging_bootstrap).
│   ├── llm_execution_causality.py # QUBE_LLM_CAUSALITY: post-inference causal report (prompt/template/stops/sampler vs live); optional LM Studio first-token diff via reference JSON.
│   ├── logging_bootstrap.py # init_llm_debug_logging(): attach LLM debug file sink; keep stdout clean.
│   ├── memory_filters.py   # Memory v6 Phase A — single source of truth for ASSISTANT_FAILURE_PATTERNS / is_assistant_failure_message / is_thin_content / detect_explicit_remember / detect_recall_intent / detect_file_search_intent / detect_narrative_intent (T3.2) / RECALL_FUSION_SYSTEM_SUFFIX / NARRATIVE_RECALL_SYSTEM_SUFFIX (T3.2) / derive_memory_tier + MEMORY_TIERS (T3.4); shared by EnrichmentWorker (extraction filter + episode summariser + tier-aware source namespacing), LLMWorker (recall / narrative fusion + system suffixes + per-route tier flags), and mcp/memory_tool (episode-aware + tier-scoped retrieval). derive_memory_tier(fact) is a deterministic pure function mapping a validated fact payload to one of preference / knowledge / episode / context based on category/subject/origin/_explicit_remember — used at store-write time to build qube_memory::<tier>::<category> sources.
│   ├── memory_negative_list.py # Memory v6 Phase C — persistent ~/.qube/memory_negatives.json of vectors for memories the user explicitly deleted in Memory Manager; EnrichmentWorker rejects extraction candidates within DEFAULT_REJECT_DISTANCE (0.20 L2) so the same memory cannot be recreated from a similar conversation. FIFO-capped at MAX_NEGATIVES=500.
│   ├── memory_usage_recorder.py # Memory v6 Phase C — process-wide thread-safe queue of (kind, memory_id) events. Producers: mcp/memory_tool.memory_search records "retrieved" per result, LLMWorker scans final text for [N] cites and records "cited". Consumer: EnrichmentWorker._maybe_drain_usage_recorder batches every USAGE_DRAIN_INTERVAL_SEC and bumps times_retrieved / times_cited_positively / last_used_at on each affected row.
│   ├── model_behavior.py # classify_model_behavior + resolve_behavior_override; load-time ablation → execution overrides (no prompt/sampling in resolver).
│   ├── model_capability_detection.py # CapabilitySignal/ModelCapabilities + hybrid pipeline: user_override -> ground_truth -> learned_registry -> curated exact/pattern -> file inference -> HF -> readme extraction -> soft defaults -> heuristics; includes normalization, pattern matching, safe README parsing, negation guard.
│   ├── model_capability_service.py # System capability orchestrator: cache-or-detect, overrides API, runtime ground-truth ingest, post-load enrichment, UI summaries, and missed-model logging.
│   ├── hf_publisher_branding.py # Trusted HF publisher allowlist + derivative/verification gating + cached model/org metadata resolver for official logos in Model Manager.
│   ├── model_override_store.py # Phase 5: ~/.qube/model_overrides.json — LearnedOverride load/save; build_prompt_bundle merges extra_stop_tokens + assistant anchor; [LLM-SELF-HEAL-APPLY].
│   ├── model_reasoning_profile.py # detect_model_reasoning_profile: tokenizer scan (first hit) + chat_template + metadata_template weak hints + name/path; _llama_cpp_model; ModelReasoningProfile + ExecutionMode; metadata only — no prompt/sampling changes.
│   ├── native_llama_chat.py # OpenAI-style message normalization + chat_format alignment for native create_chat_completion; in Auto mode, prefers ChatML for NVIDIA/Nemotron when available, otherwise keeps GGUF Jinja fallback.
│   ├── native_llama_inference.py # Extra stop strings + kwargs for native create_chat_completion (merged with formatter stops; LM Studio–style guards).
│   ├── native_llm_debug.py # QUBE_LLM_DEBUG: reconstructed prompt logging, stop merge helpers, EOS/BOS, inference request JSON logs (LM Studio parity tooling).
│   ├── native_meta_leading_strip.py # Native streaming path: optional strip of brief meta-instruction openers at start of assistant text (conservative).
│   ├── native_sampler_gt.py  # Sampler ground truth: wraps Llama.generate during inference; prompt-token assembly mirrors llama-cpp-python _create_completion.
│   ├── native_token_trace.py # QUBE_LLM_TOKEN_TRACE: JSON logs — live delta re-tokenization, post-hoc, vs sampler ground truth (see native_sampler_gt).
│   ├── network.py          # Port scanning (Ollama/LM Studio detection).
│   ├── prompt_ablation_harness.py # NON-PRODUCTION: diagnostic ablation scenarios (prompt/stop variants, leakage heuristics, AblationReport); run_ablation_test uses create_completion(prompt=...) — not the app chat path; infer_override_from_ablation + store_override → ~/.qube/model_overrides.json; [LLM-SELF-HEAL].
│   ├── prompt_integrity_validator.py # Prompt structure checks, LM Studio parity scoring, QUBE_LLM_REFERENCE_JSON / first_sampler_token_ids (validation only); attaches model_reasoning_profile_detected + execution_mode (resolved policy mode) to validation JSON (metadata).
│   ├── prompt_template_router.py # infer_template_type + apply_reasoning_injection + build_prompt_bundle; template_override + model_override_store layers; [LLM-TEMPLATE] / [LLM-TEMPLATE-OVERRIDE] / [LLM-SELF-HEAL-APPLY] / [LLM-PROMPT-ROUTER]; validation/log prefetch (chat path unchanged).
│   ├── redacted_thinking_filter.py # Stream filter for <redacted_thinking> blocks (DeepSeek-R1–style; internal engine path).
│   ├── stream_repetition_guard.py # StreamRepetitionGuard: observer-only tail check over streamed deltas; trips on N consecutive identical short whitespace atoms (e.g. runaway [W] [W] [W] …) so llm_worker can cancel the generation instead of waiting for the 15 min wall cap.
│   ├── richtext_styles.py  # App-wide link palette / rich text helpers.
│   ├── qube_tooltip.py     # Custom app-owned tooltip pipeline (QubeApplication notify interception + transparent host/rounded shell) for consistent cross-theme rendering on frameless Linux.
│   ├── system_capabilities_store.py # Isolated system SQLite + JSON artifacts under ~/.qube/system_data (capabilities.db with ground_truth_capabilities table, curated_registry.json, learned_capabilities.json, missed_models.json); survives user DB/LanceDB resets.
│   └── template_override.py # Phase 4: detect_template_override (phi / Nemotron / Mistral name heuristics) — extra stops + assistant anchor in build_prompt_bundle only; [LLM-TEMPLATE-OVERRIDE].
├── api/                    # HTTP service layer
│   └── model_capabilities_api.py # FastAPI endpoints for listing capability summaries, full capability detail/debug, overrides, runtime-loaded capability ingestion, enrichment, and offline export bundle.
├── workers/                # Background Event Loops (QThreads)
│   ├── audio_worker.py     # Captures audio, runs OpenWakeWord.
│   ├── stt_worker.py       # Runs Faster-Whisper on audio byte chunks.
│   ├── llm_worker.py       # Streams LLM tokens, RAG cascade; internal native path uses NativeLlamaEngine.get_execution_policy() for thinking strip/display (policy-driven stream filters) and applies a NVIDIA/Nemotron-specific internal prompt policy tuned for completeness without exposing reasoning. T3.3: per-turn enrichment gate — _reset_turn_enrichment_flags + _mark_skip_enrichment + _mark_explicit_remember_mode; enrichment_context_ready payload carries skip_enrichment / enrichment_mode (full|explicit_only|skip) / skip_reason; trips fire on stream-repetition-guard (external HTTP + native stream), web-tool failure sentinel on WEB/INTERNET/HYBRID routes, pipeline error, and assistant-failure final text; explicit-remember turns emit enrichment_mode=explicit_only so the bypass still seeds while the extractor LLM call is skipped. T3.2 narrative recap override: detect_narrative_intent(self.prompt) (after explicit-remember + file-search gates) forces decision={route=memory, prefer_episode=True, strategy=narrative_recap}; memory_search is called with prefer_episode=True; when any sources survive retrieval, NARRATIVE_RECALL_SYSTEM_SUFFIX is appended to the system prompt so the LLM prefers [EPISODE]-labelled sources over atomic facts. T3.4 per-route tier flags: every memory_search call now passes include_preference / include_knowledge / include_episode / include_context — CHAT (route=NONE) runs a cheap preferences+context retrieval (top_k=3, MemGPT-style core memory, skipped on explicit-remember + file-search), MEMORY/HYBRID add include_knowledge=True, narrative adds include_episode=True.
│   ├── native_llama_engine.py # QThread: Llama load/unload/generate; load-time behavior ablation (skipped if get_override has persisted self-heal) + model_behavior overrides; coalesces queued rapid load bursts so latest pending model wins; build_prompt_bundle in _prepare_validation_and_logs; detect_model_reasoning_profile; get_execution_policy(); [LLM-DEBUG] reasoning_profile + execution_policy + llm_model_behavior_profile; post-inference: token trace → causality → counterfactual (env-gated).
│   ├── hf_model_search_worker.py # Background Hugging Face Hub model search (GGUF-oriented filtering) for the Model Manager browse list; returns branding payloads and supports paged UI consumption.
│   ├── hf_readme_worker.py # Fetches repository README markdown from Hugging Face for the Model Manager detail pane.
│   ├── hf_repo_files_worker.py # Lists .gguf file paths in a model repo via Hub API for quantization selection.
│   ├── model_download_worker.py # Streams GGUF downloads from Hugging Face with Content-Length disk pre-check, cooperative cancel, and .part file cleanup.
│   ├── internet_worker.py  # QThread for non-blocking web search queries (mcp/internet_tool.search_internet).
│   ├── enrichment_worker.py # Memory v6 — atomic memory extraction + storage. Phase A: typed schema (subject/source_role/durability/provenance_quote) with explicit NEGATIVE prompt examples (person_name stub, no-internet) and server-side _validate_fact dropping system/assistant/third_party-without-knowledge/non-long_term/thin/failure-pattern/missing-provenance candidates; explicit-remember bypass via detect_explicit_remember; assistant failure messages scrubbed before _build_prompt. Phase B: enqueue contract takes per-turn payload (last_user_msg_id / last_assistant_msg_id / rag_chunk_ids); base_payload threads source_session_id / source_message_ids / origin / links_to_document_ids; embedding-based _assign_cluster (CLUSTER_JOIN_DISTANCE=0.30) with keyword fallback; two-stage _judge_contradiction (Jaccard fast-path + LLM judge → duplicate|contradiction|complement). Phase C: payload carries times_retrieved / times_cited_positively / last_used_at / last_reflected_at / flagged_for_review; _maybe_drain_usage_recorder flushes the MemoryUsageRecorder queue every USAGE_DRAIN_INTERVAL_SEC; _maybe_run_decay_sweep every 24h re-scores usefulness/decay and purges rows below DECAY_PURGE_THRESHOLD=0.15; pre-extraction reject against memory_negative_list at distance < DEFAULT_REJECT_DISTANCE. T3.3 tool-aware fences: enqueue payload honours skip_enrichment (short-circuit in run() with INFO log) and enrichment_mode (full / explicit_only / skip) threaded through _process_turn → _extract_and_store; explicit_only skips the extractor LLM call but keeps the explicit-remember bypass seeding. Cadence-driven usage drain + decay sweep still run regardless. T3.2 episodic summaries: after every _extract_and_store atomic-fact flush, _maybe_summarise_session bumps per-session turn counter + idle-gap check and fires _summarise_session_now when counter >= EPISODE_SUMMARY_TURN_CADENCE (8) OR idle > EPISODE_SUMMARY_IDLE_SEC (15 min); _build_episode_prompt / _parse_episode_response produce a single-paragraph SUMMARY + TOPICS line (SKIP means no write); summary capped at MAX_EPISODE_CHARS (800), rejected if thin_content / assistant_failure / negative-list hit; _replace_episode_row writes exactly one row per session at source="qube_memory::episode::<session_id>" with category="episode", origin="session_summary", topics[], episode_reason, replacing any prior episode for that session in place (no new LanceDB columns — all fields live inside the JSON text payload). T3.4 tier-aware source namespacing: atomic facts now land in ``qube_memory::<tier>::<category>`` where tier = derive_memory_tier(fact) (preference / knowledge / context — episodes keep their T3.2 per-session namespace). The tier is the only thing on the source string that changed; payload schema, vector, chunk_id stay identical so no LanceDB migration is required on fresh installs.
│   ├── memory_reflection_worker.py # Memory v6 Phase C — periodic LLM self-audit of stored memories. Wakes every REFLECT_INTERVAL_SEC (6h), batches BATCH_SIZE (10) least-recently-reflected non-flagged rows older than MIN_REFLECT_AGE_SEC (7d), asks the same titler LLM to label each as durable_user_fact / third_party_stub / system_claim / transient / unclear, sets flagged_for_review on anything other than durable_user_fact, and stamps last_reflected_at + reflection_label. T3.2: category=="episode" rows are skipped by the reflection scan — episode summaries are regenerated by the enrichment worker on cadence/idle triggers and are not the kind of "durable user fact" the judge is meant to rate. T3.4 structural labels: _structural_label_for runs BEFORE the LLM judge and returns "tier_mismatch" (source=qube_memory::preference::% but subject != user) or "orphan_knowledge" (source=qube_memory::knowledge::% with no provenance_quote, no links_to_document_ids, and not explicit_remember origin) — both added to VALID_LABELS so _parse_label survives an LLM echo round-trip; LLM judge only runs when structural check returns None. NEVER auto-deletes — flagged rows surface in MemoryManagerView for the user to confirm.
│   ├── tts_worker.py       # Manages universal TTS adapters (Piper/Kokoro) and audio queues.
│   ├── title_worker.py       # Generates titles for the conversations list (bundled Qwen 0.5B performs it)
│   ├── intent_router.py       # Uses semantic vector embeddings for intent routing instead of rigid keywords, while cognitive_router manages load and thresholds.
│   └── ingestion_worker.py # Parses, chunks, and embeds documents in the background.
├── rag/                    # Retrieval-Augmented Generation Engine
│   ├── embedder.py         # llama-cpp-python embedding engine with Nomic v1.5 GGUF; probes GPU first with CPU fallback.
│   ├── store.py            # LanceDB interface (Disk-native, zero-copy vector storage).
│   ├── chunker.py          # Semantic text splitting (1500 chars / 150 overlap).
│   └── parsers.py          # Document parsers (PDF, EPUB, TXT, MD, Wiki dumps).
├── mcp/                    # Model Context Protocol Interfaces
│   ├── rag_tool.py         # Disk-backed search function called by the LLM interceptor. Phase B: emits chunk_id as composite "<source>::<chunk_int>" on every UI source so EnrichmentWorker can persist links_to_document_ids and memory_tool can later expand them back to the originating RAG chunks.
│   ├── internet_tool.py    # Web search functionality
│   ├── memory_tool.py      # Retrieves stored facts via hybrid score (semantic distance + confidence + strength + Phase C decay) with strict token budgets. Phase B: auto-expands payload.links_to_document_ids into additional type="rag" sources up to MAX_LINK_EXPANSIONS_PER_MEMORY / TOTAL / CHARS budgets so a recall query against a thin memory still receives the originating document context. Phase C: every returned memory is reported to MemoryUsageRecorder as "retrieved" and carries memory_id in the UI source dict so LLMWorker can later record [N] cites against the same id. T3.2 episode-aware retrieval: memory_search(..., prefer_episode=True) adds +0.35 to final_score for category=="episode" rows (so session summaries outrank atomic facts on recap turns), bypasses the proper-noun gate for episode rows (narrative queries carry no entity tokens), and prefixes the inline memory_context bullet with "[EPISODE]" so the LLM — following NARRATIVE_RECALL_SYSTEM_SUFFIX — can tell the session summary apart from atomic facts. T3.4 tier-scoped WHERE: memory_search(..., include_preference / include_knowledge / include_episode / include_context) composes a tier-aware LanceDB WHERE via _build_tier_where_clause (_TIER_TO_SOURCE_PREFIX maps each tier to qube_memory::<tier>::%); include_context also pulls legacy qube_memory::% rows so pre-T3.4 installs keep working. prefer_episode=True implicitly re-enables the episode LIKE even if include_episode=False. When every tier flag is off the clause falls back to "source LIKE 'qube_memory::%'" to avoid accidentally returning zero rows.
│   ├── router.py           # Maintained as a legacy fallback for the cognitive_router, this component provides stable, deterministic query routing using fixed cosine-similarity thresholds and hardcoded semantic anchors.
│   ├── cognitive_router.py # Manages adaptive query routing by dynamically adjusting retrieval thresholds based on real-time system latency, load penalties, and conversation intent drift. Phase B: optional recall_centroid (installed by LLMWorker via set_recall_centroid) drives _score_recall_intent; when recall_active, route is forced to HYBRID (after web override) so recall-style queries always fuse memory + RAG.
│   ├── router_self_tuner.py # Acts as an autonomous feedback loop that continuously tunes cognitive routing sensitivities based on real-time telemetry (latency and hit rates) to penalize inefficient tool usage.
│   ├── router_telemetry.py # Maintains a lightweight, in-memory queue of recent routing events to track latency, hit rates, and route distributions for real-time performance monitoring.
├── models/                 # Local AI Weights (Organized by function)
│   ├── llm/                # User LLM GGUFs for the internal engine (managed by Model Manager).
│   ├── stt/                # Faster-Whisper weights.
│   ├── tts/                # Piper/Kokoro voices and configs.
│   ├── embeddings/         # Placeholder folder; embedding model is loaded as a GGUF via llama-cpp-python.
│   └── wakeword/           # OpenWakeWord detection models.
├── data/                   # LanceDB vector storage directory.
├── system_data/            # Seeded system capability artifacts (copied to ~/.qube/system_data at runtime)
│   ├── curated_registry.json # Curated exact + pattern rules for capability inheritance.
│   ├── example_models.json # Example payloads for capability detection.
│   ├── learned_capabilities.json # Learned local capability registry (self-heal layer) updated from runtime truth.
│   ├── missed_models.json  # Seed list for missed-detection feedback loop.
│   └── schema.sql          # System capabilities SQLite schema.
├── tools/                  # Utilities package (python -m tools.<module>): llm_prompt_diff.py, view_llm_logs.py, run_ablation.py (prompt ablation CLI — diagnostic only).
```
